{"comments":"Fluid flow behavior classification — Newtonian and non-Newtonian fluids.\n\n## What is Flow Behavior?\n\nFluids are classified by how their viscosity responds to shear stress:\n\n- **Newtonian**: Constant viscosity regardless of shear rate\n  (water, oils, most gases)\n\n- **Non-Newtonian**: Viscosity changes with shear rate or time\n  - Shear-thinning: viscosity decreases under stress (ketchup, paint)\n  - Shear-thickening: viscosity increases under stress (cornstarch slurry)\n  - Bingham plastic: yields only above threshold stress (toothpaste)\n  - Thixotropic: viscosity decreases over time under stress (yogurt)\n  - Rheopectic: viscosity increases over time under stress (rare)\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nAt billion-agent scale, flow behavior determines:\n- How fluids respond to stirring, pouring, spreading\n- Haptic feedback during fluid manipulation\n- Simulation accuracy for complex fluids\n- Rendering of non-Newtonian splashes and flows\n\n## Mathematical Models\n\n- Power law: τ = K × γ̇ⁿ\n  - n < 1: shear-thinning\n  - n = 1: Newtonian\n  - n > 1: shear-thickening\n\n- Bingham: τ = τ₀ + μ × γ̇ (above yield stress τ₀)\n\n- Herschel-Bulkley: τ = τ₀ + K × γ̇ⁿ (generalized)\n\n## Related Papers\n\n- Stream Function Solver (Newtonian fluids)\n- Fire-X (multi-phase with varying properties)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[146,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[146,3]},"title":"Newtonian"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[147,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[147,3]},"title":"ShearThinning"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[148,20],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[148,3]},"title":"ShearThickening"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[149,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[149,3]},"title":"BinghamPlasticType"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[150,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[150,3]},"title":"Thixotropic"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[151,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[151,3]},"title":"Rheopectic"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[152,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[152,3]},"title":"Viscoelastic"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Fluid","FlowBehavior"],"FlowBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[154,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[154,1]},"title":"eqFlowBehavior"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Fluid","FlowBehavior"],"FlowBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[155,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Fluid/FlowBehavior.purs","start":[155,1]},"title":"ordFlowBehavior"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{